    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Isolepis fimbriata are fever and rheumatism, due to its diuretic and anti-inflammatory properties, which help to reduce swelling and alleviate pain in joints and muscles. Its antiseptic and antimicrobial properties also make it effective in treating skin infections such as eczema and dermatitis, while its expectorant properties help to relieve respiratory issues like bronchitis and asthma by thinning mucus and promoting its expulsion from the lungs. Furthermore, the plant's antioxidant and immunomodulatory properties enable it to help manage autoimmune diseases like lupus and rheumatoid arthritis by regulating the immune system and reducing inflammation. Additionally, Isolepis fimbriata's diuretic properties can aid in treating urinary tract infections by increasing urine production and flushing out bacteria from the urinary system. Its antiseptic properties also make it useful in treating wound infections and promoting wound healing by preventing the growth of bacteria and other microorganisms.",
