    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Isolepis fimbriata are anti-inflammatory, exhibiting potential in alleviating symptoms of arthritis and other inflammatory conditions, thanks in part to the presence of saponins and flavonoids. Additionally, this plant has been found to possess antimicrobial properties, which can aid in the treatment of infections and wound healing, attributed to the presence of volatile oils and phenolic compounds. Furthermore, Isolepis fimbriata has been shown to have antioxidant properties, helping to protect cells from oxidative stress and damage, due to the abundance of flavonoids and phenolic acids. Its immunomodulatory properties have also been identified, allowing the plant to potentially stimulate the immune system and increase its response to pathogens, a function associated with the presence of saponins and glycosides. Moreover, Isolepis fimbriata has been found to exhibit anti-cancer properties, with its bioactive compounds such as flavonoids and saponins showing potential in inhibiting the growth of cancer cells and inducing apoptosis.",
