    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Isolepis fimbriata are flavonoids, phenolic acids, alkaloids, terpenoids, and saponins, which contribute to its medicinal properties. Flavonoids, such as kaempferol and quercetin, have been found to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, while phenolic acids like ferulic acid exhibit antimicrobial and antioxidant properties. Alkaloids, including aucubin and isolepstin, have been reported to have anti-inflammatory and hepatoprotective effects, while terpenoids, such as isoleptic acid, display antimicrobial and antioxidant activities. Saponins, present in Isolepis fimbriata, have been found to have anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects. These constituents work synergistically to provide Isolepis fimbriata with its therapeutic benefits, making it a valuable medicinal plant in traditional medicine.",
