    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Isolepis fimbriata are derived from its roots and leaves, with the primary purpose being to utilize its purported anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. Infusion and decoction are used to prepare a tea from the dried plant material, which can be taken orally to potentially alleviate symptoms of colds, fever, and other minor health issues. A tincture is prepared by steeping the plant material in a solvent, such as ethanol, to create a concentrated liquid extract. Salve is prepared by infusing the plant material in a fatty solvent, like olive oil, to create a topical cream for potential skin issues. These preparations are often used in traditional medicine to address various health concerns, but more research is needed to confirm the effectiveness of Isolepis fimbriata preparations.",
